    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Give and Take on Napster</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Andrew Miller letter on June 29 article says Napster does not act as a host for files on its servers but merely allows people to share</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Regarding the article about Napster, I have a few comments about copyright concerns: ''Napster says no. But ask a copyright lawyer, and the answer is most likely to be yes.''</p>
        <p>Napster does not act as a host for files on its servers. All it does is allow people to share. Does that mean that a message board would be illegal if people use it to exchange sites that have illegal content? Absolutely not. Napster is a very useful tool.</p>
        <p>ANDREW MILLER  Princeton, N.J.</p>
      </block>
